Xiao D is a pharmacist in a hospital in Wuhan. His mother is an examination doctor in another hospital. He has two cousins, one is a nurse in an infection ward and the other is a first-line policeman.

During the outbreak, six people in the family have a small group, everyone in the group every day to report their body temperature, each other said safe, and small d three people were separated in three different "home" , relying on the phone, to confirm each other's situation. Families, who are fighting their way back to their posts, are waiting to be reunited after the outbreak.

I am a native of Wuhan, Hubei Province. I work in the Pharmacy Department of a new Guanding Hospital. Besides me, there are three other people in my family who are in the front line of this epidemic. My mother is a laboratory doctor in another hospital. One of my two cousins works as a nurse in an infection ward, the other one's a cop.

Being in a medical family, our family might be sensitive to information. At that time, when the south China seafood market was said to have mass pneumonia, and the whole market was disinfected, we ourselves began to do protection, i bought some basic protective products such as masks and gloves. The masks are ordinary medical masks. I didn't have the habit of wearing a mask before going to and from work. Sometimes I just wear it when I think of it. After I heard the news, I began to wear a mask everyday.

After the new coronavirus was officially diagnosed, our hospital began to do some intensive training, explain the transmission of the new coronavirus, teach us how to prevent, how to avoid hospital infection. Because there will be rest, duty or live far colleagues, so the training lasted a week, every afternoon, the content is the same, did not listen to the past listen.

Many departments have also integrated, facial features, dermatology these departments are closed, all changed to infection department. Now we ask everyone in the hospital to wear a mask, gloves and a hat, and then we don't have any protective clothing because it's not as dangerous as the first line, if you can get your own goggles, protective clothing, you wear it. You wear it.

Our hospital is still very many patients with the new coronavirus, several floors are their wards. Most of the new coronavirus pneumonia patients we come into contact with at pharmacies are mild, and their drug lists are labeled "confirmed" or "suspected" , but you can tell by looking at the prescriptions. Use them now.

On the day of the siege, I was particularly impressed. I switched shifts that day, 24-hour shifts, from 8:00 a.m. the first day to 8:00 a.m. the next. Then the first morning in the subway to see the 10 o'clock closure of the news, the whole person is silly, not worried about the closure of the city, or think about how I will go home the next day.

We own a few friends have a group, we are still inside the joke, I also joke said a sentence, "how do I go back tomorrow Ah. ". Later that night I got a call from a friend who asked me, "are you coming back tomorrow? ". I said, "I'll probably have to wait until this afternoon. One of my colleagues will take me back. "

My friend, he didn't think it was safe to be in the hospital at a time like this, so he told me he'd pick me up the next morning. At that time because I do not know what I have (virus) , I said he did not come, but he insisted on coming to pick me up, said good protection.

That night, I went to work on the crying, really did not expect, because the day is a joke, how to say, he does not dislike me, I was very moved.

After the outbreak, I was afraid of the virus, also afraid of contagion, this time has been living alone. So was my mother. She was in the Examination Department of another hospital, and because of the distance, she was afraid of bringing the virus home to infect my father, to infect me, so she didn't go back to live there either. She stayed with her grandparents temporarily, it's like the three of us aren't going back to the same house for a while.

Mom doesn't really talk to me about her work, just that she's tired. The family has a group, usually she will take a picture of work, that is, wrapped up in a very tight picture, sometimes wearing a mask is torn.

She's going to give us some information about nucleic acids, what's wrong with them, what's wrong with them, what's wrong with them, what's wrong with them, what's wrong with them, what's wrong with them, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you, what's wrong with you.

Because I was in a different hospital and didn't go back to the same home, I hardly saw my mother after the epidemic. The only time I saw her was last week when I felt a bit sick in my throat, but that day I didn't get the medicine, so my mother prescribed the medicine in her hospital, and bring it to me tonight. When they met, she wrapped like a Zongzi, I also wrapped like a Zongzi, two people mask, gloves, hats, glasses are wearing neatly, even the face can not see. Mom gave me some medicine, bought me some food, gave me my stuff and left.

During this period, I basically kept in touch with her online, and every day we would report to each other that we were safe. That is, I asked her, "how are you feeling today? " , she said, "fine. " Then I would check my temperature again, and she might say, oh, I forgot. I'm going to measure it now.

My cousin's work permit from the infection ward

In addition, my cousin, my aunt's daughter, worked as a nurse in the infection ward. Their hospital was a designated hospital at first, and then she was in the smoking department, so she was in the infection ward at the beginning of the epidemic, and spent the New Year's Eve in the ward.

She's wrapped up tighter every day, and she has to wear two or three layers of gloves, because she has to be in direct contact with the new patient. Because the protection was too strict, she breathed very hard, now also can not go home, in the nearby hotel unified quarantine, every day to eat a little food, rest less, also sleep not good.

Cousin married, children in Primary School, now the children do not see each other, are brother-in-law in the care of a person, at most is in the group video. Sometimes she works nights, but she can't see much, because she can't use her cell phone in her hazmat suit, so she has to make time to talk when she gets off work.

We cheer each other on in the family group

We are all in a group, chat in the process of feeling her good state of mind, showing more optimistic, the biggest feeling is still tired, from the voice inside can feel her tired.

My uncle's daughter, my other cousin, was also a cop on the front lines, but I didn't ask her what she did, because there was something going on at home, and it wasn't convenient to ask her too much.

Our family had an early New Year dinner, so we didn't get together again during the New Year. In the past, we always have dinner together on GRANDPA's birthday. This year, we don't have dinner together. We just video, have a meal and clink glasses. That's it. Since several of US are on the epidemic line, the rest of the family will be worried, but we are also used to this situation, every day we chat quite normal.

For the first line of the mother, two cousins, the most want to say is to protect themselves. The meal can be eaten later. The most important thing is that the family is safe.

In fact, I learned medicine from very early to say, because when I was a child always see my mother wearing a white coat feeling very yearning, later choose professional also do not know what to choose a medical science, said it is also a coincidence.

It was scary at first, because it was the first time in more than 20 years that something like this had happened, even though it hadn't been confirmed that the disease was contagious. But after the confirmation, I wasn't afraid, because I still have to go to work, you do this job, don't think so much.

Of course, I was not in the front line, perhaps my psychology and them (front-line medical staff) psychological and different. But to put it bluntly, the hospital is not safe inside, we must do a good job of protection.

On the day of the blockade, I bought several thousand yuan of medicine, my mother also bought several thousand yuan of medicine, after coming back to distribute everywhere. Because we all know that if you are not feeling well at this time, do not go to the hospital, because it is easy to cross-infection. When a few friends meet to give me something or for some other reason, I give it to them. Like masks, disinfectant, things like that, I started buying them a long time ago, and then a little bit of this and a little bit of that.

During the outbreak of this period, there are old people died at home, but it is not clear whether it is because of the new crown, there are students they all diagnosed. People around me have come to ask for help, and when they do, they feel powerless and want to help others, but they can't help.

My words actually all along did not look on the net the information, my information source is generally big Chu Net, the medical net these official, the specialized media. Because there's so much information on the Internet. A lot of friends will send a message in the group, I give them every day in refuting rumors. This is not right, this is not right, this is not right, this why is not right, that why is not right, please do not send again. In a few hours he'll wind up with a new one, and then he'll tell him it's probably wrong, too.

As soon as I looked up, I could still see a lot of people walking and walking their dogs. I think this is a long-term battle, Hubei side is also the most serious, or there is a security risk. Years have passed, do not know what the next step is, hard to judge.

The Doorman hasn't been the same to me in a while. The original night home, no key card, trouble he opened the door to say a couple of uncle. A while ago, I went into the community to take my temperature. I might see that my protective equipment was different from others. I was wearing a hat, glasses, gloves and a mask. He asked me, "did you just get off work? " I said, "yes. " Then he took my temperature, ask Me if I have (epidemic prevention) card, I was about to take off gloves, he said, "No, no, go in. ".

When this is over, I think I'm GonNa go home and have dinner. I went home to get my things, and I stood in the doorway, afraid to come in. My Dad was home, and my dad cried when I left, and he said I was too much, and he wouldn't even come in. I don't talk much with my dad. Every day, I say, "you rest early, don't go out to play. " Then he says, "ok, I didn't go out to play. " I don't know if he's telling the truth or not.

Now the state of the whole family is to report a safe day in the group, and then continue to struggle in their respective posts. Because the only thing you can really do now is to protect yourself, because when you're sick alone, there's no way anyone else can stay out of it. Protect Yourself, and persuade those around you to protect yourself.

After the outbreak, I wanted barbecue. I wanted barbecue so bad. Have some friends over for a barbecue and some wine. It's great.

During the outbreak of this period, there are old people died at home, but it is not clear whether it is because of the new crown, there are students they all diagnosed. People around me have come to ask for help, and when they do, they feel powerless and want to help others, but they can't help.

My words actually all along did not look on the net the information, my information source is generally big Chu Net, the medical net these official, the specialized media. Because there's so much information on the Internet. A lot of friends will send a message in the group, I give them every day in refuting rumors. This is not right, this is not right, this is not right, this why is not right, that why is not right, please do not send again. In a few hours he'll wind up with a new one, and then he'll tell him it's probably wrong, too.

As soon as I looked up, I could still see a lot of people walking and walking their dogs. I think this is a long-term battle, Hubei side is also the most serious, or there is a security risk. Years have passed, do not know what the next step is, hard to judge.

The Doorman hasn't been the same to me in a while. The original night home, no key card, trouble he opened the door to say a couple of uncle. A while ago, I went into the community to take my temperature. I might see that my protective equipment was different from others. I was wearing a hat, glasses, gloves and a mask. He asked me, "did you just get off work? " I said, "yes. " Then he took my temperature, ask Me if I have (epidemic prevention) card, I was about to take off gloves, he said, "No, no, go in. ".

When this is over, I think I'm GonNa go home and have dinner. I went home to get my things, and I stood in the doorway, afraid to come in. My Dad was home, and my dad cried when I left, and he said I was too much, and he wouldn't even come in. I don't talk much with my dad. Every day, I say, "you rest early, don't go out to play.
